  "difficultyLevel": 3,
  "lyrics": "As I see the sun come up over that mountain way, I contemplate the way that I can hike the rest of the trail, up the valleys and past the rocks, down the side roads of your favorite block, all the way past all your traps and all your maps, and then find myself on my way to you, oh yeah, I'm on my way baby, on my way to you, now we take a little trip on down the road, me and my big old truck, and you and your sandals head blowing, right in front of me, is the most gorgeous beautiful life I think I've ever seen, play the Eagles loud, turn the radio up with your favorite song, getting along with it all, you've got John Prine counting his clay pigeons, in the back of the bus, singing all a song of love baby, time gets better when you lock it down and just stop, look around and hear the sound, community laughing, hands clapping and you're back to the start, as the sun rises up here, top that mountain, of looking for the ways up to your spot, through all your trapping and all your grudges, I'm finding my way up right to where you are baby, I'm finding my way up right to where you are, oh baby baby, right where you are",
